g.aria-label: Fraction of wastewater that is treated then re-added to the supply.In Israel, most wastewater is treated, and of what is treated, most is reintroduced into thesupply. Given the severe level of water scarcity in Israel, it is unclear the extent to whichIsraeli water recycling can economically be replicated elsewhere in the world. Data sources:Israeli Water Authorityfor Israeli figuresandUNfor the rest of the world.United Nations World Water Assessment Programme. "The United Nations World Water Development Report2014: Water and Energy". Paris, UNESCO.2014.Water Authority of Israel. "The Wastewater and Treated Effluents Infrastructure Development in Israel".2015.
